data.enText: a place, person or thing that you get sth from
renewable energy sources

data.chText: 你们当地的图书馆就是很好的资料来源。
data.enText: Your local library will be a useful source of information.

data.chText: 他们的主要收入来源是什么？
data.enText: What is their main source of income?
a person, book or document that provides information, especially for study, a piece of written work or news

data.chText: 他拒绝说出消息的来源。
data.enText: He refused to name his sources.

data.chText: 政府方面昨天透露，削减可能势在必行。
data.enText: Government sources indicated yesterday that cuts may have to be made.
source material

data.chText: 历史学家在研究中使用大量的原始资料和二手资料。
data.enText: Historians use a wide range of primary and secondary sources for their research.
a person or thing that causes sth, especially a problem
a source of violence
a source of confusion
the place where a river or stream starts
the source of the Nile
at source
at the place or the point that sth comes from or begins
Is your salary taxed at source (= by your employer) ?
to get sth from a particular place

data.chText: 我们商店里卖的肉均从英国农场购进。
data.enText: We source all the meat sold in our stores from British farms.
at source
at the place or the point that sth comes from or begins
Is your salary taxed at source (= by your employer) ?

tr: a facility where something is available
anything that provides inspiration for later work
a document (or organization) from which information is obtained
example: the reporter had two sources for the story

tr: a publication (or a passage from a publication) that is referred to
example: he carried an armful of references back to his desk
he spent hours looking for the source of that quotation

tr: the place where something begins, where it springs into being
example: the Italian beginning of the Renaissance
Jupiter was the origin of the radiation
Pittsburgh is the source of the Ohio River

tr: anything (a person or animal or plant or substance) in which an infectious agent normally lives and multiplies
example: an infectious agent depends on a reservoir for its survival

tr: someone who originates or causes or initiates something
example: he was the generator of several complaints

tr: (technology) a process by which energy or a substance enters a system

example: The writer carefully sourced her report

tr: get (a product) from another country or business
example: She sourced a supply of carpet
They are sourcing from smaller companies

value.def: The source of something is the person, place, or thing which you get it from.

example.ex: ...over 40 per cent of British adults use television as their major source of information about the arts...
example.tran: 40 %以上的英国成年人把电视当作获取艺术文化信息的主要途径。

example.ex: Renewable sources of energy must be used where practical...
example.tran: 必须在可行的地方使用可再生能源。

example.ex: Tourism, which is a major source of income for the city, may be seriously affected.
example.tran: 作为该市主要收入来源的旅游业可能会受到严重影响。

value.def: In business, if a person or firm sources a product or a raw material, they find someone who will supply it.

example.ex: Together they travel the world, sourcing clothes for the small, privately owned company...
example.tran: 他们一道走遍世界各地，为那家私营小公司寻觅服装货源。

example.ex: About 60 per cent of an average car is sourced from outside of the manufacturer.
example.tran: 一辆普通汽车上大约有60%的部件是由制造商以外的其他供应商提供的。

example.ex: ...furniture sourced from all over the world.

value.tran: 寻找(产品或原料的)货源

example.ex: The union is particularly concerned at the sourcing of products abroad.
example.tran: 该联盟尤其关注海外的产品货源。

value.def: A source is a person or book that provides information for a news story or for a piece of research.

example.ex: Military sources say the boat was heading south at high speed...
example.tran: 军方称这艘船当时正高速向南行进。

example.ex: She quotes secondary and primary sources without distinction.
example.tran: 她对二手资料和一手资料的引用毫无区别。

value.tran: 消息来源;消息人士;(论文中引文的)出处，原始资料

value.def: The source of a difficulty is its cause.

example.ex: This gave me a clue as to the source of the problem.
example.tran: 这件事给我提供了找出问题根源的线索。

value.def: The source of a river or stream is the place where it begins.
